<h2 id="1-models-of-interaction-some-terms-of-interaction">1. Models of interaction: Some terms of interaction</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>domain</strong> â€“ the area of work under study
    <ul>
      <li>e.g. graphic design</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>goal</strong> â€“ what you want to achieve; <strong>or</strong> final result to be achieved
    <ul>
      <li>e.g. create a solid red triangle</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li><strong>task</strong>â€“ how you go about doing it; structured set of related activities undertaken in a sequence â€“ ultimately in terms of operations or actions
    <ul>
      <li>e.g. â€¦ select fill tool, click over triangle</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>goalê³¼ taskê°€ ì‚¬ìš©ë  ë•ŒëŠ” ë§ˆêµ¬ ì„ì—¬ì„œ ì‚¬ìš©ëœë‹¤.(contextë¥¼ íŒŒì•…í•´ì•¼ í•¨)</li>
  <li>note â€¦
    <ul>
      <li>use of terms differs a lot especially task/goal !!!</li>
      <li>systemâ€™s language vs. userâ€™s language</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

